RefParameter.Name: OB_Product_State_active
RefParameter.Description:
Product states to protect memory content from debug access.
Open: User Flash open (TZ secure and non-secure open) External access (debug) N and NS enabled (~RDP0).
Provisioning: Provisioning - immutable root of trust is being installed. nv-Open if TZEN is disabled.
iROT-provisioned: The immutable root of trust is installed. (~RDP 0.5).
TZ-Closed: State for debugging the NS application. Debug is restrained to non-secure areas.
Closed: State for running a secure application. Debug disabled, regression is possible.
Locked: Transition to other state, policy change or debug is not permitted.
Regression: The temporary state initiated by the debug authentication system in transition to nv-Open.
NS-Regression: The temporary state initiated by the debug authentication system in transition to nv-Closed_secure.

RefParameter.Name: OB_BOR_level
RefParameter.Description:
Bits 1:0 BOR_LEV[1:0]: Brownout level option status bit
These bits reflects the power level that generates a system reset.
00: BOR OFF, POR/PDR reset threshold level is applied
01: BOR Level 1, the threshold level is low (around 2.1 V)
10: BOR Level 2, the threshold level is medium (around 2.4 V)
11: BOR Level 3, the threshold level is high (around 2.7 V)

RefParameter.Name: OB_BORH
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 2 BORH_EN: Brownout high enable
0: disable
1: enable

RefParameter.Name: OB_IO_VDD_HSLV
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 16 IO_VDD_HSLV: High-speed IO at low VDD voltage configuration bit.
This bit can be set only with VDD below 2.7 V.
0: High-speed IO at low VDD voltage feature disabled (VDD can exceed 2.7 V).
1: High-speed IO at low VDD voltage feature enabled (VDD remains below 2.7 V).

RefParameter.Name: OB_IO_VDDIO2_HSLV
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 17 IO_VDDIO2_HSLV: High-speed IO at low VDDIO2 voltage configuration bit.
This bit can be set only with VDDIO2 below 2.7 V.
0: High-speed IO at low VDDIO2 voltage feature disabled (VDDIO2 can exceed 2.7 V).
1: High-speed IO at low VDDIO2 voltage feature enabled (VDDIO2 remains below 2.7 V).

RefParameter.Name: OB_IWDG_STOP
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 20 IWDG_STOP: IWDG Stop mode freeze option configuration bit.
When set the independent watchdog IWDG is in system Stop mode.
Disable: Independent watchdog frozen in system Stop mode.
Enable: Independent watchdog keep running in system Stop mode.

RefParameter.Name: OB_IWDG_STDBY
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 21 IWDG_STDBY: IWDG Standby mode freeze option configuration bit.
When set the independent watchdog IWDG is frozen in system Standby mode.
Disable: Independent watchdog frozen in Standby mode.
Enable: Independent watchdog keep running in Standby mode.

RefParameter.Name: OB_BOOT_UBE
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 29:22 SWAP_BANK [7:0]:Unique boot entry control, selects either ST or OEM iRoT for secure boot.
This information is also used by RSS to boot through ST-iROT when in Open PRODUCT_STATE.
Can only be changed in product states open for debug like Open and also in Provisioning. SECBOOT_LOCK must be disabled to change.
OEM-iRoT: User Flash selected.
ST-iRoT: System Flash selected.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SWAP_BANK
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 31 SWAP_BANK: Bank swapping option configuration bit.
SWAP_BANK option bit is used to configure whether the Bank1 and Bank2 are swapped or not.
This bit is loaded with the SWAP_BANK bit of FLASH_OPTSR_CUR register after a reset.
Disable: Bank1 and Bank2 not swapped.
Enable: Bank 1 and bank 2 swapped.

RefParameter.Name: OB_IWDG_SW
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 3 IWDG_SW: : IWDG control mode option configuration bit.
Disable: IWDG watchdog is controlled by hardware.
Enable: IWDG watchdog is controlled by software.

RefParameter.Name: OB_WWDG_SW
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 4 WWDG_SW: WWDG control mode option configuraton bit.
Disable: WWDG watchdog is controlled by hardware.
Enable: WWDG watchdog is controlled by software.

RefParameter.Name: OB_nRST_STOP
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 6 nRST_STOP: Core domain Stop entry reset option configuration bit.
Disable: A reset is generated when entering Stop mode on core domain.
Enable: No reset generated when entering Stop mode on core domain.

RefParameter.Name: OB_nRST_STDBY
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 7 nRST_STDBY: Core domain Standby entry reset option configuration bit.
Disable: A reset is generated when entering Standby mode on core domain.
Enable: No reset generated when entering Standby mode on core domain.

RefParameter.Name: OB_TZEN
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 31:24 TZEN[7:0]: Trust Zone enable configuration bits.
This bit enables the device is in trust zone mode during an option byte change.
OB_TZEN_DISABLE:0xC3: Trust zone disabled.
OB_TZEN_ENABLE:0xB4: Trust zone enabled.
This Option byte cannot be set throught CubeMX

RefParameter.Name: OB_TZEN
RefParameter.Description:

This bit enables the device is in trust zone mode during an option byte change.
OB_TZEN_DISABLE:0xC3: Trust zone disabled.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM1_ECC
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 10 SRAM2_ECC: SRAM1 ECC detection and correction disable.
Disable: SRAM2 ECC check enabled.
Enable: SRAM2 ECC check disabled.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM1_RST
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 9 SRAM2_RST: SRAM1 erase upon system reset.
Disable: SRAM2 erased when a system reset occurs.
Enable: SRAM2 not erased when a system reset occurs.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM2_ECC

Enable: SRAM2 ECC check disabled.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM2_RST
RefParameter.Description:

Disable: SRAM2 erased when a system reset occurs.
Enable: SRAM2 not erased when a system reset occurs.

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM3_ECC
RefParameter.Description:

RefParameter.Name: OB_SRAM13_RST
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 2 SRAM13_RST: SRAM1 and SRAM3 erase upon system reset.
Disable: SRAM1 and SRAM3 erased when a system reset occurs.
Enable: SRAM1 and SRAM3 not erased when a system reset occurs.

RefParameter.Name: OB_BKPRAM_ECC
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 4 BKPRAM_ECC: Backup RAM ECC detection and correction disable.
Disable: BKPRAM ECC check enabled.
Enable: BKPRAM ECC check disabled.

RefParameter.Name: OB_NSBOOTADD_Address
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 31:8 NSBOOTADD[23:0]:Unique boot entry address.
These bits reflect the Secure UBE address.

RefParameter.Name: OB_NSBootLock
RefParameter.Description:
Bit 7:0 NSBOOT_LOCK[7:0]: Non secure Boot lock.
A field locking the values of SWAP_BANK, and NSBOOTADD settings.
Disable: The SWAP_BANK and NSBOOTADD can still be modified following their individual rules.
Enable: The NSBOOTADD and SWAP_BANK are frozen.

PossibleValue.Diagnostic: Unlock is possible in Open, Provisioning and Regression

RefParameter.Name: OB_OTP_LOCK_active
RefParameter.Description:
Bits 31:0 LOCKBL[31:0]: OTP block lock.
Block n corresponds to OTP 16-bit word 32 x n to 32 x n + 31.
LOCKBL[n] = 1 indicates that all OTP 16-bit words in OTP Block n are locked and attempt to program them results in WRPERR.
LOCKBL[n] = 0 indicates that all OTP 16-bit words in OTP Block n are not locked.
When one block is locked, it is not possible to remove the write protection.
LOCKBL bits can be set if the corresponding bit in FLASH_OTPBLR_CUR is cleared
